< Date>
1466487054084< /Date>
<rate>4</rate>< Text>
Wasn't sure what to expect here as my coworkers seemed to think it was just so-so compared to their other normal choices in the area.

The atmosphere was good. It was a quiet Monday evening. I ordered the Wedge Salad and the Ultimate Mixed Grill (stuffed shrimp, grilled shrimp, scallops, salmon). Both were items were very tasty! Got the wedge with some extra bleu cheese crumbles (which makes it better automatically) The scallops were very well cooked, though could have used some kind of light sauce. The salmon was a little dry, but not too bad. Prices overall weren't bad for the area, I've seen worse.

The only thing that disappointed me slightly was the limited number of times we saw our waitress during the meal. Probably 4 times total not including ordering, food delivery, and checks, and the place was empty. She was very friendly, however. Oh, and they didn't have Dr. Pepper, my favorite soft drink. :'(

Will come back. Would recommend to a friend.< /Text>

<rate>3< /rate>< Review>
Made a reservation for Thanksgiving dinner for 6 PM for a party of 4. They were busy, and after a 15 minute wait, we decided to sit at an empty table in the bar. Not a problem, we liked being around the TV's and the action.
Waitress was good, attentive to our needs. Food was mediocre at best. Last year at Thanksgiving I was in Bozeman MT and went to Ted Turners Montana Grill for Thanksgiving. Had a great meal with turkey and all the fixings, including desert, for $25. The meal at McCormick was $27.5. The beans were good and warm, the rest of the meal felt like I was eating in a high school cafeteria. The scoops of stuffing and mashed potatoes were institutional at best. The stuffing for the 2 of us that ate the turkey was cold, and when we told the waitress she promptly brought us hot stuffing, although it was still dry and tasteless. The cranberry was OK, too bad after two teaspoons the tiny amount they gave us was gone. My friend asked for more and got some from the waitress. The turkey was similar to the kind your purchase at the supermarket when they take out a turkey and slice it, not the thick and meaty pieces I am used to for Thanksgiving, and certainly not as good as my meal at the Montana Grill. And to top it off, desert was not included. All in all, for such a nice restaurant the meal was not what I expected, and I will not go back.<//Review>

< Review>
This location has everything you'd want or need in a FedEx office, but my review is directed towards the staff. They're generally helpful and knowledgeable about everything you'd need help with, and my personal experience interacting with them was more than pleasant. This is the first Google review I've ever posted, and the honesty and integrity of the staff at this location prompted me to do so.

I brainlessly left my wallet sitting in front of one of the computers in the workstation... and didn't realize it until around 5 hours later. After stressing out got me nowhere, I retraced my steps and realized this store was the last place I remembered seeing it. Lo and behold, the staff had secured my wallet, and it was returned to me without a single dollar missing. And this SOB was PACKED with cash.. an admittedly stupid amount to carry on me but I hadn't had a chance to deposit it yet. Anyway, it was incredibly refreshing to see a display of honesty like this.. maybe I'm cynical and too focused on all the bad in the world, but I wasn't expecting to see my wallet again, and had completely given up hope that the cash would be in it if it was returned. My faith in humanity has been restored, thanks to a FedEx. Strange but true</Review>

< text>
Usually, I think of FedEx Office/ UPS Store/ Printing and Shipping Places as an unbearable drama of mishaps, but this place proved me so wrong. Had a question about placing my online order for prints, called the store, the employee had me explain what I wanted and then gave me the store email to send the file to and said she would take care of the order from there. Less than 24 hours later I got a call it was finished! Everything was exactly how I wanted, reasonably priced (worth noting other print shops had quoted double for the same job), and the pickup was super easy and friendly. Store was clean and well staffed. Would go back here.<//text>

< review>
I called every high rated shop around Anaheim as I'm fairly new to the area, to replace my timing chain on my Cadillac and all of them said the same thing "We don't do that here to much work"  and local GM Dealer ship wanted 5,000 dollars to do the job, luckily found Anaheim Auto Repair and Muffler care, and Langston immediately told me he would do it for 1400 and it would take 2 days... I ordered parts two weeks before the date we set to fix it, and I dropped it off to him on a Tuesday after missing my set date on Monday, he had had no problem with it and took my keys , and he ended up calling me back  in a ONE DAY for me to come and pick up my car, Very professional! He showed me my old parts, and my car was running so much better than before! they fixed it and I was able to pass my smog test, and register my car on time! Thank you so much guys at Anaheim auto repair and muffler care! continue the honest customer service I experience with you your team! I recommend this auto shop to anyone!< /review>

< Review>

I have brought my vehicle in for oil changes, Langston is very attentive of customers and quickly receives you and does the job with efficiency.

I recently checked in for a vehicle repair, I believed my vehicle needed new brakes and new joint axle. Langston then informs me that there is a major issue with my transfer case which was causing the noise I so thought it was from the wheels brakes. This only happens to AWD (all wheel drive) vehicles. We ordered 3 appetizers 3 main dishes,  Roasted mushrooms, Heirloom tomatoes, tar tar beef, Diver Scallops, Halibut, Papardelle. The only outstanding dish was Roasted mushrooms, Heirloom tomatoes and tar tar beef was just ok, but all 3 main dishes was all dried the taste was ok but seems like these 3 dishes was not served right away because it was really dried out.
The waitress might had been worried that we were not very happy about the main courses so she decided to automatically charged us 20% gratuity by written it on my credit card charged slip. I didn't complain because I normally tip my server about 20% anyway but I just don't like to be forced by written it on, I hope it was not the restaurant policy because it was only 3 of us dining,  I typically see other restaurants charges for gratuity for party of 6 or more.</Text>

< Review>
Its been 4 years since we've eaten here but I wanted to share our experience. In 2015 we lost our home in the Valley Fire. Our anniversary was just days after that. Someone we know recommended the Harvest Table. The friend gave them a heads up we were coming. They treated us so special! I will never forget their kinds words and special service on our anniversary. The food was wonderful. I would recommend the grits as a meal all by itself, Yummy! We ate in the outdoor patio under the beautiful Redwood trees. Thank you so much Harvest Table for everything you did for us!<//Review>

<username>Lucy</username><Time>1560753281515<//Time><rating>2</rating><Review>DON’T ORDER SPRING RISOTTO!!! (Unless you no longer have teeth, taste buds, and a big appetite!)

Nice place, good service, but the food that I had was ridiculously overpriced with nothing much in it!

I ordered the Spring Risotto, and I am giving it zero star. Menu description said it has english pea, short rib and charred onion bouillon. I was expecting at least a couple of big chunks of tender short ribs on top of the risotto. What I got on my plate was about 1/4 cup of risotto with spring onion strips on top. Where’s the beef????? I found 3 very small disintegrating  pieces of meat underneath, the biggest piece of which was less than a square inch wide, about 1-1/2 cm thin! The other two meat particles were even smaller and thinner!  And I am not exaggerating. $22 for all that! I’ve been to several high-end restaurants, but this is the most ridiculously rip-off dish I’ve ever had!

My only consolation... i liked the grape-seed oil dip that they serve with the bread and the good service of the waiters/waitresses, so I’m giving them four stars for that.< /Review>< Pics>

We then quickly leaving the place, the server followed  and opened the door for us, said: Please DO NOT come back, we don't welcome you and we have the right to REFUSE to serve anyone.

We were quite upset with it, they didn't admit the their fault but also slammed the door for communication and corrections.

I can't believe a restaurant can treat customer like this and we will never come back again.</text>
<Response>None< /Response></record></dataset><record>
<pictures>None</pictures><Time>1534797128563</Time>< Review>
I'll start by saying the service here is top notch, especially for a Vietnamese restaurant. Two people were always watching if I happened to glance up, and I was served promptly and graciously. The food here is very palatable, and it arrive quickly and fresh to my table. My issue with this place is that the food does not taste like Vietnamese food to me. I was still craving grilled pork when I left, although the grilled pork I had here was not bad. There was fresh white onion slices and served on my place along with the veggies, but that was a first for me. Another variable was price. For a rice plate (grilled pork with imperial roll combo, $11.95 as of posting) and a drink (Vietnamese iced coffee, $4.50 as of posting) my total came to $17.93, leaving me to leave put an end evening tip, leaving me a whole $20 lighter when I left. Knowing I can get a similar meal for $3-4 cheaper in my neighborhood in SF and knowing I would leave with my flavor cravings satiated, I will most likely only return to try their pho. From the looks of orders from other tables, maybe that is what they do best. For my first experience, I would say excellent service, about 25% overpriced, and a rather different flavor combination than usual for their rice dishes. Being an avid Vietnamese food lover, I will return to try again.< /Review>

<Rating>5<//Rating>< Review>
I cannot talk more highly of this place!  I love Pho quite a bit and heard nice things about Thai crepes so I had to give it a try.  Their menu is very concise with lots of options (which sounds contrary but trust me, they have it all).

Started with the sprint rolls and got the combo meal which includes a small bowl of Pho (which is a pretty big bowl) as well as a choice of 3 types of meat from a list of about 7 things and then extra stuff on the side.  All for like $14.95!  Great deal and I guarantee you will be taking food home for later.

They said in about 2 weeks (so around the start of April) they will be hiring someone to work the crepe station and our server claims they will offer savory and dessert crepes as well as bubble teas.  So we will be heading back very soon!

We got 2 apps, numerous sakas, 2 combo meals and it was a little over $50.< /Review>

<UserId.>118228460365704229149</UserId.>< username>
Drew Trager<//username>
<time>1509639421934<//time>< Rating>
4< /Rating>
< Review>
Pho Vinh has become my go-to spot for pho in San Carlos. My favorite dish is pho tai and if I'm hungry I'll also order the fresh spring rolls. For eat-in, the service is really quick and I'm usually finished with my meal in less than 20 minutes. For takeout, they do a really nice job packaging all the ingredients separately so everything is still really fresh by the time you get home. The pho is consistently delicious so I'll be back again soon. I've given them 4 stars because they charge a pesky $0.50 service fee if your order is less than $15 and you want to use a credit card. Bring cash and you're golden.<//Review>

< Review>
I suspected my home had termites, and requested a termite inspection.  The Orkin inspector quickly identified the issue as crickets, not termites.  I was relieved.  The home damages and costs associated with termites vs crickets is huge.  So bonus points to Orkin for not trying to up sell me on termites!

I scheduled Orkin for quarterly home perimeter treatment (crickets plus other insects). I received auto-texts reminding me of the scheduled appointment, a text when the technician  was headed my way, and another text when the tech arrived (these texts are appreciated).  The tech was on-time, professionally dressed, super friendly and informative.  You can tell this tech enjoys his job, which reflects well on the franchise management.

Of note, besides spraying the outside edges of the house and inside the garage (I asked not to spray the home interior for now), he also cleared all cobwebs around the house and patio eaves.  This is his benchmark for future visits to see if spiders are returning or not.  If he sees new webs in the future, he said he’d treat those areas.  Impressive!!

Overall, with just the one inspection and the one treatment, I’m totally satisfied!  (And I’m already seeing crickets scurry from their hiding places!)</Review>

<text>Scammers. Be aware.

At first I was positively impressed by Orkin’s fast response; I had an ant infestation and called them on a Thursday evening after 9pm, hoping to leave a voice message and schedule a visit for two days after the call, but a representative answered my call right away and scheduled a visit for the next day. The same person talked about the plans they offered and I choose the one time visit (that would give me 30 days to be sure the ants were gone) he insisted on putting me on the monthly plan, but I insisted on the one time visitation and hang the phone certain that he had honored my request.

The representative who came to my house, Danny; told me that my order was designated as monthly and that I should wait to cancel it after few days but I insisted on changing the order to what I have requested and paying the price for it; Danny told me that he would change the order and keep the price and since they had made the mistake. Danny contacted me a week later to know if that were ants,  and since there still were some inside the outside planters, he offered to send me his availabilities for the next week, but never did.

The next Monday, since I didn’t hear from him, I called the company and requested the follow up visit, complained about his disappearance and they schedule my visit for the next Wednesday.  The same person came to my house again to reapply the venom.

A week later he sent me a text message, asking about the ants and I explained that there were still ants and asked if he could come the next day, he ignored my message for 24 hours, responding it Thursday evening that he could be at my house between 10 am and 12pm the next day, Friday.
